com.echsylon.atlantis

Interface MockResponse.Filter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultResponseFilter, RandomResponseFilter, SerialResponseFilter
    Enclosing class:
    MockResponse

    public static interface MockResponse.Filter
    This interface describes the mandatory feature set to provide a mocked response. Implementing classes are responsible for picking a mock response from a given list of available responses. Any state machine etc is also in the scope of the implementing class.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      MockResponse findResponse(List<MockResponse> mockResponses)
      Returns a mocked response of choice.

    • Method Detail

      • findResponse

        MockResponse findResponse(List<MockResponse> mockResponses)
        Returns a mocked response of choice. May be null, in which case the calling logic is responsible for deciding what to do.
        Parameters:
        mockResponses - All available mock responses to pick a candidate from. Null and empty lists are acceptable.
        Returns:
        The mock response candidate.
